# Git Workflow

## Commit Messages

```
<type>: <description>

<optional body explaining why>
```

Types: `feat`, `fix`, `refactor`, `docs`, `test`, `chore`, `perf`, `ci`

- Imperative mood, under 72 characters for the subject line.
- Body explains *why*, not *what*. The diff shows what.
- One logical change per commit. Do not bundle unrelated changes.
- No emdashes in commit messages.

## Branch Names

`feature/short-description`, `fix/short-description`, `refactor/short-description`

## Pull Requests
- Analyze full commit history with `git diff [base-branch]...HEAD`, not just the latest commit.
- Summary: 1-3 bullet points describing what changed and why.
- Include a test plan with specific checklist items.
- Every PR that changes behavior must include corresponding test changes.
